                          persist reducer

                          Hight order redux reducer that has only 2 possible actions

                          #Usage

                          import { persistReducer } from '@cranium/cache'
                          import { composeReducers } from '@cranium/redux-helpers'
                          import { combineReducers } from 'redux'
                          composeReducers(
                          {},
                          combineReducers({
                          users,
                          casrs,
                          }),
                          persistReducer(JSON.parse(process.env.CACHE_STATE_PERSIST_KEYS)),
                          )

                          #API

                          persistReducer(persistKeys)

                          persistKeys is an optional Array<String>. Than mean that this data should not be deleted after RESET_STORE action.

                          tip

                          You can use CACHE_STATE_PERSIST_KEYS from .end file

                          #Actions

                          #INIT_STORE

                          This is redux action that will be trigerred automatically when redux store will be initialized from cache.

                          note

                          This is automatical action you should not be worry to call this action by your own. cacheMiddleware will take care to get data from store on your app initialized state and call this action when data will be retrived. This is common case for React-Native apps where AsyncStorage has async API

                          #RESET_STORE

                          This is redux action that will clear all redux store exept persistKeys. This is most common action on logout

                          import { reset } from '@cranium/cache'
                          import { connect } from 'react-redux'
                          function LogoutButton({ reset }){
                          return (
                          <button onClick={reset}>
                          Logout
                          </button>
                          )
                          }
                          export default connect(null, { reset })(LogoutButton)
